1
00:00:00,310 --> 00:00:01,970
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:03,680
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:16,620 --> 00:00:18,790
Hey, you got a minute?

4
00:00:19,890 --> 00:00:21,060
Sure.

5
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:31,970
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

6
00:00:32,140 --> 00:00:35,810
Wow, this BBQ place is popular.
I hear it's very reputable, right?

7
00:00:36,310 --> 00:00:39,910
Yes. The place is spotless.
I wouldn't have to change a thing.

8
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:42,680
My dad and I will check it out later
and sign the contract.

9
00:00:43,480 --> 00:00:44,520
With Father?

10
00:00:45,020 --> 00:00:46,180
You're not going
with your boyfriend?

11
00:00:46,750 --> 00:00:49,720
What are you talking about?
I told you I don't have a boyfriend.

12
00:00:49,790 --> 00:00:53,430
Oh, come on!
I bet your boyfriend made this.

13
00:00:53,590 --> 00:00:56,660
No! I made this myself.

14
00:00:58,630 --> 00:01:01,630
Come on. Just give me
your boyfriend's date of birth.

15
00:01:01,870 --> 00:01:05,400
I'm going to see the shaman later
about Hyun Bin anyway,

16
00:01:05,470 --> 00:01:07,270
so I can see
if you two are a good match.

17
00:01:07,770 --> 00:01:09,610
Forget it. You're too much.

18
00:01:10,110 --> 00:01:14,410
By the way, is it true Taehan's VP
really likes Hyun Bin?

19
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:15,480
Do you think they have a chance?

20
00:01:16,980 --> 00:01:20,520
I'm not a huge fan
of Dr. Han Seong Mi,

21
00:01:20,750 --> 00:01:24,090
but I do trust her. If she got
the impression they were dating,

22
00:01:24,160 --> 00:01:25,220
they probably are, right?

23
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:30,230
True. As an expert and psychiatrist,
she'd know at a glance.

24
00:01:31,460 --> 00:01:35,030
I hope Hyun Bin will settle down
in Korea for good.

25
00:01:35,670 --> 00:01:39,470
Anyone hearing you talk like that
would think he's your own son.

26
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,010
What? He's like my own son.

27
00:01:42,010 --> 00:01:43,740
The same goes for Eun Bin and Ji Hu.

28
00:01:43,740 --> 00:01:47,550
Come on. Still, it's different
than having a biological child.

29
00:01:47,910 --> 00:01:49,950
You wouldn't know
because you've never had children.

30
00:01:51,780 --> 00:01:54,290
Why do I hear the cry of a newborn?

31
00:01:55,090 --> 00:01:56,620
Because you raise another child,

32
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,760
you think
you'll escape punishment...

33
00:01:58,860 --> 00:02:00,390
for leaving
your own flesh and blood?

34
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:04,030
A bond you have abandoned...

35
00:02:04,530 --> 00:02:07,470
will always return
to exact its price.

36
00:02:08,130 --> 00:02:09,170
Mark my words.

37
00:02:11,070 --> 00:02:13,170
(OnBike)

38
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:40,870
What?

39
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Hold on a second.

40
00:02:58,020 --> 00:02:59,150
Here, take my number.

41
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:01,650
That's okay. I'm not hurt.

42
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:04,390
I'm making it clear
I gave you my number.

43
00:03:05,660 --> 00:03:07,460
Shouldn't you be apologizing first?

44
00:03:09,830 --> 00:03:12,430
- Excuse me?
- You jumped out without looking.

45
00:03:15,030 --> 00:03:17,140
Okay, after hearing that tone,
I've changed my mind.

46
00:03:17,540 --> 00:03:19,370
I'm going to need your contact info
as well.

47
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:22,010
In case you try to report me
for a hit-and-run later.

48
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:23,510
Give me your number.

49
00:03:25,210 --> 00:03:27,350
Have you always lived your life
being fooled?

50
00:03:27,780 --> 00:03:29,910
There are many good people
in this world.

51
00:03:31,050 --> 00:03:32,380
That's really sad.

52
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:37,490
What did she just say to me?

53
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,660
Did you just bad-mouth me?
Hey, you! Get back here!

54
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:42,060
Hey, you! Wait!

55
00:03:42,390 --> 00:03:44,000
The nerve of that brat.
An elder is speaking to her.

56
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Unbelievable.

57
00:03:48,230 --> 00:03:50,170
Mom.

58
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:58,280
It's barely gone down.

59
00:03:58,380 --> 00:04:00,910
She buys such expensive stuff
and is too cheap to use it.

60
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:04,750
It's a shame to let it go to waste.
I should help her use it up.

61
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:07,750
What else does she have?
Let's see...

62
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:10,290
What?

63
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:12,260
What's this?

64
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,760
What else did she hide in here?

65
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,660
- Yang Eun Bin!
- My gosh! You scared me!

66
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,960
Are you using my makeup
behind my back again?

67
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:23,840
I'm going to be on TV too.
We should both look our best, right?

68
00:04:23,940 --> 00:04:27,670
My stuff isn't right for your age.
Instead of using mine,

69
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:31,440
- let's go to the spa together.
- Really? Yes!

70
00:04:31,610 --> 00:04:34,350
Wait, what's that?
Why is it wrapped up so tightly?

71
00:04:34,410 --> 00:04:37,850
Oh, this is just a soap set
I got as a gift for the holidays.

72
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:40,650
Wow, that's some fancy wrapping
for soap.

73
00:04:51,530 --> 00:04:52,860
Gosh, what do I do?

74
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,400
Vice President.

75
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:36,140
Perhaps you can put your phone down
during the meal.

76
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:38,610
It's just...

77
00:05:39,710 --> 00:05:42,950
Isn't this hilarious?
The "Just Roll Challenge."

78
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:44,920
(Just Roll Challenge)

79
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:48,750
I know, right? Raffling gift cards
just for falling over...

80
00:05:48,850 --> 00:05:50,420
It's such a novel idea.

81
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:53,090
How did you come up
with an idea like this?

82
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,490
Exactly.

83
00:05:54,490 --> 00:05:57,630
An official social media challenge
to reenact your mother's fall.

84
00:05:58,430 --> 00:06:02,470
Since it was a hot topic,
I pitched a viral campaign.

85
00:06:02,670 --> 00:06:05,100
"It won't rip
even if you fall like that."

86
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:06,700
"The stretch is incredible."

87
00:06:06,770 --> 00:06:10,440
"Taehan clothes are so durable."
We're getting comments like that.

88
00:06:10,710 --> 00:06:11,810
Oh, right.

89
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,010
But you did get
your mother's permission, right?

90
00:06:14,150 --> 00:06:17,820
Of course.
She was happy and felt like a model.

91
00:06:18,220 --> 00:06:21,250
Maybe I should give it a try.
I can do front and back somersaults.

92
00:06:21,250 --> 00:06:22,350
Sure.

93
00:06:22,650 --> 00:06:24,620
I'm sure
the executives would love that.

94
00:06:25,660 --> 00:06:26,660
Whatever.

95
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:29,090
Is there anything fun going on?

96
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,630
Hey! Where are those two?

97
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:34,500
Ms. Gong and Mr. Park?

98
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:38,340
Director Yang's family and mine
have made up.

99
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:42,770
- Really?
- Yes. His mother helped me...

100
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:45,840
avoid disciplinary action, you know.
So as a thank you, my grandmother...

101
00:06:45,910 --> 00:06:47,980
invited them over for her birthday,
and we worked things out.

102
00:06:48,450 --> 00:06:51,280
Our fathers will be
on "Human Theater" together.

103
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:55,150
- Wow. Hey, that's great news!
- Right? It is, isn't it?

104
00:06:55,420 --> 00:06:58,790
Go ahead and tattle to the VP again,
and we'll see what happens.

105
00:07:01,130 --> 00:07:04,560
I've been swamped lately,
so I let it slide,

106
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:09,270
but tell the VP about my family
one more time, and I'll kill you.

107
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:13,400
Okay, I get it. All right?

108
00:07:13,970 --> 00:07:17,880
But promise to keep me updated
on any progress between you two.

109
00:07:19,610 --> 00:07:21,610
Hey, that's such a low blow.

110
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:29,650
But are you really volunteering
to be the VP's spy...

111
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:32,090
for the future of
the Fashion Division?

112
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:36,290
Yes, well, of course.
What other reason would there be?

113
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:41,270
No, well... You two are so close.
I was wondering if you were...

114
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:43,400
on your way to becoming
Taehan's son-in-law or something.

115
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:47,370
Oh, that's a fresh perspective.

116
00:07:47,570 --> 00:07:50,310
You know,
I've never even considered that.

117
00:07:50,410 --> 00:07:53,410
Why not?
You could have a crush on her.

118
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,950
She is a wonderful person,
after all.

119
00:07:57,420 --> 00:07:59,280
I can't argue with that, but...

120
00:08:00,050 --> 00:08:02,050
It's just that, for some reason...

121
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:04,090
she feels like a big brother to me.

122
00:08:05,090 --> 00:08:07,990
The kind who carries
a heavy burden all alone.

123
00:08:08,330 --> 00:08:09,930
Like an older, close friend
who just happens to be rich?

124
00:08:10,460 --> 00:08:13,560
The kind who uses work as an excuse
to pry into others' love lives...

125
00:08:13,630 --> 00:08:15,900
and live vicariously through them.
That kind of pitiful big brother.

126
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,040
That's my big brother.

127
00:08:23,370 --> 00:08:25,110
Yes, brother...
I mean, yes, Vice President.

128
00:08:26,310 --> 00:08:29,950
What was that all about?
Why meet with Ms. Gong in private?

129
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,480
I'm dying to know.

130
00:08:32,820 --> 00:08:35,950
Well... I'm afraid
I won't be able to give you...

131
00:08:36,020 --> 00:08:38,190
any more reports from now on,
Vice President.

132
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:41,860
Are you breaking our alliance?

133
00:08:42,060 --> 00:08:45,100
If I were breaking it, I wouldn't be
reporting it to you, would I?

134
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,760
But you didn't report anything.

135
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:50,330
Well, I was reporting that
I won't be able to report anymore.

136
00:08:53,070 --> 00:08:56,270
- You're clearly hiding something.
- No, not at all.

137
00:08:56,540 --> 00:08:57,540
Fine.

138
00:08:58,480 --> 00:09:01,050
Then as a token of my gratitude
for last time,

139
00:09:01,380 --> 00:09:03,480
I'll pay a visit
to Pacu Nacho's mother,

140
00:09:03,780 --> 00:09:06,150
and I'll try to help things along
between those two.

141
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:09,050
- No, please don't, Vice President.
- Why not?

142
00:09:09,490 --> 00:09:13,760
Why won't anyone let me do anything?
There's no fun in life anymore.

143
00:09:15,490 --> 00:09:19,100
So you're sure Mr. Park
won't tell the VP anything now?

144
00:09:19,330 --> 00:09:22,470
Yes. I threatened to kill him.

145
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:26,340
My gosh, that's scary. Will you
kill me too if I step out of line?

146
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,470
Come on.

147
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:30,980
Hold on a second.

148
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:32,340
(Doctor Han Seong Mi)

149
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:37,180
- Yes, Doctor Han Seong Mi.
- I'm with a patient. Why the calls?

150
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:43,520
I've only called you twice.
And this is about work.

151
00:09:44,060 --> 00:09:46,120
Do you have any time this week,
by any chance?

152
00:09:46,590 --> 00:09:47,590
Why?

153
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:51,330
You need to come in for a fitting
before your photo shoot next week.

154
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:54,330
We need to go over the concept,
pose references, and...

155
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,970
Tomorrow's the only day I'm free.

156
00:09:59,570 --> 00:10:03,610
- Tomorrow's cutting it a bit close.
- You should've called sooner.

157
00:10:04,310 --> 00:10:07,750
Just schedule it for tomorrow.
Director Yang said he'd fit me in.

158
00:10:08,180 --> 00:10:10,080
What? Hello?

159
00:10:11,050 --> 00:10:14,350
Wow. She had her say
and hung up again. Seriously.

160
00:10:15,420 --> 00:10:19,020
I'm telling you. The world is fooled
by Dr. Han Seong Mi.

161
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:22,090
What do you mean?
I think she's honest...

162
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:24,160
and really straightforward.
I like that.

163
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:27,530
You like that? Thanks to her,
I'm stuck working late now.

164
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,070
Why does it have to be tomorrow?

165
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:31,900
Oh, well...

166
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:34,440
I was going to sign the contract
at Hyegyeong Department Store today,

167
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:37,540
and then take you out
to that Argentinian restaurant.

168
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:40,850
Right. Just go with the VP then.

169
00:10:41,110 --> 00:10:43,080
I'm sure she's been
feeling neglected lately.

170
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:46,620
Neglected? Are you kidding?
After she called my parents...

171
00:10:46,650 --> 00:10:48,350
and caused that huge scene?

172
00:10:49,220 --> 00:10:52,160
There were some bumps in the road,

173
00:10:52,220 --> 00:10:54,460
but thanks to her,
our families get along now.

174
00:10:55,830 --> 00:10:59,100
True.
For people who get along so well,

175
00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:01,670
it's crazy
they spent 30 years as enemies.

176
00:11:02,530 --> 00:11:05,800
They're signing the "Human Theater"
contract over lunch today.

177
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:10,070
My dad must be ecstatic.

178
00:11:11,610 --> 00:11:13,480
(Yang Dong Ik)

179
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:19,750
(Gong Jeong Han)

180
00:11:21,650 --> 00:11:24,560
Filming will take
approximately 2 to 3 weeks.

181
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:26,660
And we'll have an initial interview
before that.

182
00:11:27,660 --> 00:11:31,360
Remember how I was the only one
who showed off my Chinese skills?

183
00:11:31,430 --> 00:11:33,130
That's right. Why do you ask?

184
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:37,470
My friend here has
a hidden gem of a talent, too.

185
00:11:38,140 --> 00:11:40,770
I see. What is it? Do tell.

186
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:43,840
What are you getting at? Seriously.

187
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:48,450
He's a great guitarist,
an incredible singer,

188
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:53,180
and a phenomenal songwriter.
His latest song is fantastic,

189
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:55,950
so I was hoping he could perform it
during the shoot.

190
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:59,990
Now that you've brought it up,
I can't really say no... Goodness.

191
00:12:00,060 --> 00:12:02,230
It's actually a duet.

192
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:05,830
That's right!
Don't we have a video of that?

193
00:12:05,930 --> 00:12:08,270
- Should I show it to you?
- Yes, please.

194
00:12:08,670 --> 00:12:12,500
- We can listen for the right time.
- Yes, of course.

195
00:12:12,770 --> 00:12:16,270
- Oh, my daughter filmed it.
- That's right! She did.

196
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,780
No rush.
Send it over when you're ready.

197
00:12:19,410 --> 00:12:24,150
One more thing. We need
signed releases from the vendors.

198
00:12:24,850 --> 00:12:28,050
We'd appreciate your help
in getting their cooperation.

199
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,420
Don't you worry about that at all.

200
00:12:31,220 --> 00:12:34,020
As president of
the Merchants' Association,

201
00:12:34,090 --> 00:12:36,790
Dr. Gong runs a tight ship
at Onjeong Market.

202
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:39,560
It's all thanks to
our vice president here.

203
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,000
The two of us have it on lock.

204
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:47,670
You...

205
00:12:48,670 --> 00:12:52,010
Look at you,
Mr. Sunny, Yang Dong Ik.

206
00:12:52,380 --> 00:12:54,350
You're just grinning
from ear to ear.

207
00:12:54,410 --> 00:12:56,950
Hey, Gong Jeong Han from
Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic.

208
00:12:56,950 --> 00:12:58,920
Look who's talking, with that grin.

209
00:12:58,980 --> 00:13:00,820
You're that happy?

210
00:13:00,890 --> 00:13:04,290
Sure, I am. Last week's
"Human Theater" episode...

211
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:05,790
had 1.5 million viewers.

212
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:08,760
Our Dong Ik is going to be
a superstar.

213
00:13:08,830 --> 00:13:10,630
You'd better start practicing
your autograph.

214
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:18,240
You two are all smiles.
Did you win the lottery?

215
00:13:19,140 --> 00:13:21,910
Meeting Dr. Gong was my lottery win.

216
00:13:23,540 --> 00:13:26,710
By the way, I heard a rumor.
Is it true...

217
00:13:26,910 --> 00:13:29,050
that Onjeong Market is going to be
on "Human Theater?"

218
00:13:29,110 --> 00:13:32,550
Absolutely. It'll be great publicity
for the market,

219
00:13:32,650 --> 00:13:34,490
so we'll need everyone's cooperation
going forward.

220
00:13:34,550 --> 00:13:36,350
- Of course!
- Sure thing. No problem!

221
00:13:36,350 --> 00:13:38,190
We're so grateful.

222
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:41,130
- Here, try one of these.
- Thank you.

223
00:13:41,190 --> 00:13:43,860
- You've done well. We're so proud.
- Thank you.

224
00:13:43,930 --> 00:13:47,970
- For our vice president, too.
- For me as well?

225
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:51,370
Jeong Han. Thanks to you,
I get to enjoy perks like this.

226
00:13:51,670 --> 00:13:54,910
- We just thought you were fussy.
- Yes.

227
00:13:54,910 --> 00:13:56,870
So we figured
you wouldn't like this.

228
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:59,880
No, that's not true. From now on,
just like you look out for me...

229
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:03,610
No, please take even better care
of Dr. Yang than you do of me. Okay?

230
00:14:03,710 --> 00:14:07,420
- Yes, for sure.
- Of course. Will do!

231
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:10,050
- We sure will.
- Right.

232
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:11,990
Right.

233
00:14:21,870 --> 00:14:24,900
(Eun Mi Hair Salon)

234
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:29,640
<i>Leaving only this longing</i>

235
00:14:37,350 --> 00:14:39,180
- No! Stop it!
- Come on, hold still.

236
00:14:39,250 --> 00:14:40,320
- I said, stop it!
- It's fine, come on...

237
00:14:41,290 --> 00:14:42,320
Are you okay?

238
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:52,930
<i>Only my longing keeps piling up</i>

239
00:14:53,430 --> 00:14:54,430
Let's use our words.

240
00:15:02,570 --> 00:15:04,640
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

241
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:16,850
Hello, it's me.

242
00:15:16,950 --> 00:15:19,890
Welcome...
Oh, do you have indigestion again?

243
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,230
It's not that.

244
00:15:21,790 --> 00:15:24,230
Did your second son get divorced?

245
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:27,360
Why do you ask?

246
00:15:27,530 --> 00:15:31,970
I saw him at the district office,
getting divorce papers.

247
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:33,840
Really?

248
00:15:34,170 --> 00:15:37,270
Well, he didn't do anything wrong,
so there's nothing to hide.

249
00:15:38,210 --> 00:15:39,380
Yes, he's divorced.

250
00:15:39,580 --> 00:15:41,710
So that's what happened.

251
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:45,750
That explains why I haven't seen
your second daughter-in-law around.

252
00:15:47,380 --> 00:15:49,250
Is it the talk of the neighborhood?

253
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:51,160
I told everyone
not to spread rumors.

254
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,790
What good comes
from that kind of gossip?

255
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:57,190
My own daughter is divorced
and living back at home with me,

256
00:15:57,590 --> 00:16:00,560
and trust me,
I hear all kinds of nasty comments.

257
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:05,540
- I'm so sorry. I had no idea.
- Oh, dear.

258
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:08,640
It's for the best they split up
before having kids.

259
00:16:11,310 --> 00:16:12,780
Anyway, that brings me to my point.

260
00:16:15,510 --> 00:16:16,510
I know, right?

261
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,520
What? Hey, Gong Dae Han.

262
00:16:20,850 --> 00:16:22,350
What are you doing,
moping around like this?

263
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:26,860
Hey! Go, Dae Han!
Hey, we signed the contract.

264
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:27,930
Here, the contract.

265
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,770
What's up with him?
Why's he acting like that?

266
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:40,440
He's just sulking.

267
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:43,770
- What's he sulking about?
- Us being friends again, obviously.

268
00:16:44,110 --> 00:16:45,910
You know he's been jealous of me
since we were kids.

269
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:49,180
- No way. I doubt that.
- What's there to doubt?

270
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:52,580
He's probably sulking,
thinking I stole his big brother.

271
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:54,820
You think so?

272
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:03,730
Hey, are you really mad at me?

273
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:07,500
Look at this guy.

274
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,430
Are you really sulking? Hey!

275
00:17:10,430 --> 00:17:11,670
Gosh, stop it.

276
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:14,140
Come on, what's gotten into you?

277
00:17:15,070 --> 00:17:16,110
You really have to ask?

278
00:17:16,570 --> 00:17:19,440
What? Is it because I went hiking
with Dong Ik without you?

279
00:17:19,780 --> 00:17:21,510
Or that we went to the bathhouse
for scrubs together?

280
00:17:21,910 --> 00:17:23,810
Hey, are you seriously upset
over something like that?

281
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:27,720
How could you sing that song
with him for Mom's birthday?

282
00:17:28,320 --> 00:17:30,820
Oh, man.
So that's what this is about?

283
00:17:31,190 --> 00:17:32,590
Hey, come on. That was just...

284
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:35,990
That was supposed to be a surprise,
that's why.

285
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:39,230
Forget it. You were always this way,
even back then.

286
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:41,470
You're not even
the slightest bit sorry.

287
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:44,100
Unbelievable. What do you mean,
"back then?" When?

288
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:46,700
When we took the bus to school,
you two always had to sit together.

289
00:17:47,140 --> 00:17:48,240
Whenever we were late,
we'd jump the wall,

290
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:50,770
and you two would leave me behind.
Don't you remember?

291
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:52,210
Yes, that's right!

292
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:55,310
You were the only one who got caught
by the disciplinary teacher...

293
00:17:55,310 --> 00:17:56,380
and had to do squats
until you dropped.

294
00:17:57,150 --> 00:17:58,180
Yes, that's right.

295
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:01,250
You promised we'd all watch
Hong Kong movies together...

296
00:18:01,450 --> 00:18:03,190
after our exams,
but you two left me out.

297
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:05,490
And you entered the singing contest,
just the two of you, leaving me out.

298
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:09,260
Wow, you remember everything,
don't you?

299
00:18:09,490 --> 00:18:13,430
I haven't hung out with Dong Ik
for 30 years, you know?

300
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:16,070
I'm just trying to make up
for all that lost time at once.

301
00:18:16,330 --> 00:18:19,070
Come on. How old are you,
acting so petty like this?

302
00:18:19,970 --> 00:18:21,870
Seriously, if I'd known
it was going to be like this,

303
00:18:22,570 --> 00:18:24,070
I would've just moved
to a different clinic.

304
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:27,080
Please.
You failed the interview anyway.

305
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:28,350
That's not true.

306
00:18:29,380 --> 00:18:32,780
What do you mean, "not true?"
Hey, Dae Han. Gong Dae Han!

307
00:18:34,350 --> 00:18:36,620
Goodness. What's with him?

308
00:18:37,390 --> 00:18:38,390
Honestly...

309
00:18:43,530 --> 00:18:46,760
You skipped breakfast and exercise.
Why the long face?

310
00:18:48,370 --> 00:18:50,530
It's nothing.
I just don't have an appetite.

311
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:52,600
Dae Han.

312
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:54,610
Yes?

313
00:18:55,170 --> 00:18:56,170
You...

314
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:58,840
How about you go on a blind date?

315
00:18:59,580 --> 00:19:00,640
Gosh, Mom...

316
00:19:01,280 --> 00:19:03,480
The ink isn't even dry
on the divorce papers yet.

317
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:05,480
What does the timing matter?

318
00:19:06,620 --> 00:19:08,450
The best way to get over someone
is to meet someone new.

319
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:12,560
I heard even Dong Suk
is already seeing someone.

320
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:18,000
Don't feel any pressure,

321
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:22,330
but I hear she's in the same boat,
so just give it a shot and meet her.

322
00:19:23,130 --> 00:19:24,500
She's a preschool teacher.

323
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,300
Mom, I'm really not interested.

324
00:19:36,950 --> 00:19:38,750
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

325
00:19:51,030 --> 00:19:52,930
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

326
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,310
Wow, it's so nice and clean.

327
00:20:01,370 --> 00:20:04,780
- We take great care of our kitchen.
- I see.

328
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:06,280
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

329
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:07,310
By the way...

330
00:20:08,510 --> 00:20:10,580
The restaurant will be sold
sooner than we thought.

331
00:20:11,450 --> 00:20:14,350
I know, right? We're not
going to get fired, are we?

332
00:20:15,450 --> 00:20:16,950
I doubt that'll happen.

333
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:20,420
It's so clean and nice.

334
00:20:23,590 --> 00:20:24,600
Oh, my!

335
00:20:25,460 --> 00:20:27,400
I didn't realize you worked here.

336
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:29,000
Yes.

337
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:32,040
I'm taking a break from school
to work part-time.

338
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:33,040
I'm counting on you.

339
00:20:34,070 --> 00:20:35,610
Then you can just help her out
from now on.

340
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:38,140
Yes, sir. I'll do my best!

341
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:42,610
Hello. I look forward to working
with you as well.

342
00:20:43,050 --> 00:20:44,880
Please just don't fire me.

343
00:20:45,620 --> 00:20:48,020
Of course. I'd love for you to stay.

344
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:50,220
Thank you.

345
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:52,060
Thank you.

346
00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:59,200
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

347
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:00,360
What do you think?
Nice place, right?

348
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:02,600
And the price is right.

349
00:21:03,230 --> 00:21:06,740
- So you like it, then?
- Of course. Thank you, Dad.

350
00:21:08,970 --> 00:21:10,310
You know...

351
00:21:10,870 --> 00:21:13,880
- What? Did you forget something?
- No.

352
00:21:14,410 --> 00:21:16,650
That student working there
looks familiar.

353
00:21:17,150 --> 00:21:19,920
- That's Dr. Gong's son.
- Not him. The young lady.

354
00:21:20,120 --> 00:21:23,390
Come on, Dad.
Why would she look familiar to you?

355
00:21:23,790 --> 00:21:24,790
Let's go.

356
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,740
Knock, knock, knock. Delivery!

357
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:46,440
What's this?
I thought you just got home.

358
00:21:47,110 --> 00:21:48,610
I wanted to surprise you.

359
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:52,780
Honestly.
But what if someone sees us?

360
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:55,690
Come on, so what if they do?
I'm your boss, right?

361
00:21:55,820 --> 00:21:57,320
Bringing food
to a coworker working late?

362
00:21:57,320 --> 00:21:58,820
People will say
I'm sweet and thoughtful.

363
00:22:01,090 --> 00:22:02,090
Here.

364
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:07,060
Some sushi that's to die for.
And for dessert, handmade fatcarons.

365
00:22:07,460 --> 00:22:11,300
I got you Oreo cream cheese
and salted caramel.

366
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,340
I'm going to gain so much weight.

367
00:22:16,170 --> 00:22:20,080
Me too. I think we're going to gain
a ton of weight when we get married.

368
00:22:20,980 --> 00:22:22,980
Will you still love me then?

369
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:27,580
Are you kidding me?
If the woman I love most...

370
00:22:27,650 --> 00:22:29,220
gets bigger, doesn't that mean
there's more of her to love?

371
00:22:30,550 --> 00:22:32,060
You know, you're convincing me.

372
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:35,060
If I hear another word
about dieting, you're in for it.

373
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:38,530
- I've never said that.
- You said it at the BBQ place.

374
00:22:38,660 --> 00:22:39,660
Did I?

375
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:45,000
By the way, when I saw your dad
at the restaurant,

376
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:46,940
he seemed to know
you have a boyfriend.

377
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:49,270
Do you think he found out
by overhearing our call that time?

378
00:22:50,110 --> 00:22:51,640
He doesn't know
it's me, though, right?

379
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:55,010
Of course not. If he knew,
do you think he'd have let it slide?

380
00:22:55,950 --> 00:22:56,950
Wait a minute.

381
00:22:57,550 --> 00:22:59,280
What did he mean by that?

382
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:00,820
Mean by what?

383
00:23:02,590 --> 00:23:06,460
Hey, for the record,
I'm all for it. Okay?

384
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:08,160
I like that guy.

385
00:23:09,430 --> 00:23:12,730
Wait a second.
He doesn't know it's me...

386
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:14,900
Then who on earth
does he approve of?

387
00:23:15,270 --> 00:23:16,370
That's what I'm wondering.

388
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:20,100
I didn't even tell my grandma
who it was, either.

389
00:23:22,210 --> 00:23:23,710
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

390
00:23:25,310 --> 00:23:27,740
What? It's already closed.

391
00:23:28,080 --> 00:23:31,250
Gosh, at this rate,
I'll forget what Woo Jae looks like.

392
00:23:32,350 --> 00:23:35,220
I really wanted to see him.
Gosh, you scared me!

393
00:23:35,450 --> 00:23:37,250
What are you doing?

394
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:40,420
I'm so sorry.
I was just really happy to see you.

395
00:23:41,530 --> 00:23:42,560
Me?

396
00:23:42,790 --> 00:23:45,160
Yes. We know each other, don't we?

397
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:47,900
I guess so,

398
00:23:48,170 --> 00:23:49,970
but it's not like we're friends.

399
00:23:50,370 --> 00:23:52,270
- Anyway, I should get going...
- Hey, wait.

400
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:54,700
Yes?

401
00:23:55,940 --> 00:23:57,640
Do you want to join me for a drink?

402
00:23:58,340 --> 00:24:00,940
I don't really know anyone
here in Korea.

403
00:24:01,550 --> 00:24:03,280
Join me. Please?

404
00:24:07,550 --> 00:24:10,690
- Can you take out the beers?
- Sure.

405
00:24:20,730 --> 00:24:22,730
Don't tell me you sleep here.

406
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,840
Yes. I sleep here.

407
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:28,070
Why? You don't have a place to stay?

408
00:24:28,370 --> 00:24:30,510
No place to sleep?

409
00:24:31,310 --> 00:24:32,680
The thing is...

410
00:24:35,010 --> 00:24:36,010
Right, I don't.

411
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:40,520
I got robbed at my guesthouse.
That's why I'm working part-time.

412
00:24:40,850 --> 00:24:44,290
I need money for the rest of my trip
and for a ticket home.

413
00:24:45,390 --> 00:24:49,060
Then why don't you just call home
and ask them to send you money?

414
00:24:49,130 --> 00:24:52,800
Why earn money the hard way?
You're almost on the street.

415
00:24:53,130 --> 00:24:55,230
But I'm an adult.

416
00:24:55,630 --> 00:24:59,440
I can handle this myself,
so why should I worry my parents?

417
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:00,500
Don't you agree?

418
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:03,440
Ouch, that hits too close to home.

419
00:25:04,510 --> 00:25:07,510
The owner has been kind enough
to let me stay here until now,

420
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:11,450
but your aunt's taking over,
so I'll have to find another place.

421
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:12,950
My aunt?

422
00:25:13,450 --> 00:25:15,390
My aunt?

423
00:25:15,690 --> 00:25:18,090
Yes. You didn't know?

424
00:25:18,360 --> 00:25:20,420
She was here
with your grandfather earlier.

425
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:23,390
I don't know.

426
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:27,860
Eun Bin. What are you doing
drinking with a friend so late?

427
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,330
No, come home now!

428
00:25:30,930 --> 00:25:35,070
Since Eun Bin isn't getting a job,
why not let her work for me?

429
00:25:35,670 --> 00:25:36,670
Absolutely not!

430
00:25:36,940 --> 00:25:38,380
Woo Jae works there.

431
00:25:38,810 --> 00:25:41,310
Come on.
Our families have made up now.

432
00:25:41,380 --> 00:25:43,080
So what if she gets close
to Woo Jae?

433
00:25:43,180 --> 00:25:46,280
Making up and becoming in-laws
are different, don't you think?

434
00:25:46,350 --> 00:25:50,050
You're overreacting.
Woo Jae isn't interested in her.

435
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:54,860
That makes it even worse!
I'm not giving Eun Bin to any man...

436
00:25:54,930 --> 00:25:56,130
unless he is absolutely dying
to be with her.

437
00:25:56,660 --> 00:25:58,530
I agree with you there.

438
00:25:59,630 --> 00:26:02,100
Then, if you want her to do
what she loves,

439
00:26:02,170 --> 00:26:04,770
why not ask Dad to invest in her?

440
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:10,510
I'm just not sure if that would
actually be helpful for Eun Bin.

441
00:26:10,640 --> 00:26:13,680
She needs to earn for herself,
even if it's just a little.

442
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:15,910
I guess you're right about that.

443
00:26:16,910 --> 00:26:20,820
Anyway, what's all this?
Making ginseng chicken soup so late?

444
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:24,750
I'm making this
to take to Hyun Bin tomorrow.

445
00:26:25,460 --> 00:26:26,460
Liar.

446
00:26:27,120 --> 00:26:28,360
You got him a talisman.

447
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:31,160
- You're taking it to him, right?
- Hey! Hush.

448
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:33,430
Go for it.

449
00:26:34,360 --> 00:26:36,130
Dong Ik's running so late.

450
00:26:36,470 --> 00:26:38,500
He's probably still with Dr. Gong.

451
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:43,040
- Those two really hit it off.
- I know. They just signed the deal,

452
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:45,340
so I wonder what
they're still holed up preparing.

453
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:50,010
You know, whoever it was that posted
that video of you falling...

454
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:51,280
We should thank them, right?

455
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:54,520
I guess
that's one way to look at it.

456
00:26:55,890 --> 00:26:59,590
Are you okay with us being on
good terms with Dr. Gong's family?

457
00:26:59,790 --> 00:27:03,860
What? Me? It's fine, I guess.

458
00:27:04,130 --> 00:27:06,730
Hey, don't worry about me.
I'm heading up now.

459
00:27:14,670 --> 00:27:15,670
Just let it go.

460
00:27:16,240 --> 00:27:19,040
It's foolish to wait for feelings
that aren't there, Gong Dae Han.

461
00:27:19,710 --> 00:27:21,310
Just let her go...

462
00:27:22,110 --> 00:27:24,110
and just wish Dong Suk the best.

463
00:27:24,380 --> 00:27:26,650
- Uncle.
- What?

464
00:27:27,020 --> 00:27:28,490
Did you use up that shampoo already?

465
00:27:28,950 --> 00:27:31,860
- And you treasured it so much.
- Right. I guess I did.

466
00:27:32,220 --> 00:27:36,260
I guess I liked it so much that
I used it too freely, not realizing.

467
00:27:36,790 --> 00:27:39,660
Oh, right.
You know the restaurant I work at?

468
00:27:39,730 --> 00:27:41,230
Eun Bin's aunt said
she's going to take it over.

469
00:27:41,830 --> 00:27:42,900
Oh, really?

470
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:47,300
"Oh, really?"
You told her about the restaurant.

471
00:27:47,470 --> 00:27:49,440
She wanted me to tell you thanks.

472
00:27:49,770 --> 00:27:51,070
Oh, she did?

473
00:27:51,810 --> 00:27:53,810
- Hey, Woo Jae.
- Yes?

474
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:58,880
When Dong Suk came by,
was she alone or with a man?

475
00:27:59,650 --> 00:28:00,920
A man?

476
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:04,620
Yes, she was with a man.

477
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:11,560
I see.

478
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:14,460
As long as she's happy,
that's all that matters.

479
00:28:16,330 --> 00:28:17,470
Farewell.

480
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:19,940
Yang Dong Suk.

481
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:36,690
You told him
never to contact you again.

482
00:28:36,950 --> 00:28:39,060
So what are you waiting for,
Yang Dong Suk?

483
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:50,470
What did Uncle say when you told him
to go on the blind date?

484
00:28:50,570 --> 00:28:51,630
He refused, didn't he?

485
00:28:52,270 --> 00:28:53,370
How did you know?

486
00:28:53,700 --> 00:28:56,770
I think Uncle has a girlfriend.

487
00:28:57,710 --> 00:28:58,710
Really?

488
00:28:59,080 --> 00:29:00,480
I'm not 100 percent sure.

489
00:29:01,380 --> 00:29:05,050
And here I was,
thinking I was being too pushy.

490
00:29:06,080 --> 00:29:09,150
Don't worry so much.
I'm sure Uncle knows what to do.

491
00:29:09,350 --> 00:29:11,420
I certainly hope so.

492
00:29:12,860 --> 00:29:15,560
Grandma, by any chance...

493
00:29:15,630 --> 00:29:18,830
Did you tell Dad I have a boyfriend?

494
00:29:19,030 --> 00:29:23,630
- No, I only told your mom.
- Gosh, you're such a traitor.

495
00:29:23,900 --> 00:29:26,200
I can't believe you.
I told you not to say anything!

496
00:29:26,270 --> 00:29:29,040
Come on, I was just curious.

497
00:29:29,270 --> 00:29:31,880
I knew your mom would meet him
at the golf lesson event,

498
00:29:31,980 --> 00:29:34,640
so I wanted her
to check him out for me.

499
00:29:35,110 --> 00:29:39,080
What are you talking about?
Do you know who my boyfriend is?

500
00:29:40,350 --> 00:29:41,720
He's that guy from your work.

501
00:29:42,420 --> 00:29:45,120
Right, but which guy from my work?

502
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:47,160
Jun Hyeok.

503
00:29:47,860 --> 00:29:48,960
Jun Hyeok?

504
00:29:49,830 --> 00:29:52,530
Jun Hyeok? Mr. Park?

505
00:29:53,860 --> 00:29:56,970
Yes. We're really close friends,

506
00:29:57,030 --> 00:29:58,400
so I can see how
she'd get the wrong idea.

507
00:29:58,970 --> 00:30:00,570
And you just left it at that?

508
00:30:00,970 --> 00:30:02,240
What else was I supposed to do?

509
00:30:02,370 --> 00:30:05,340
What do you mean?
You should've corrected her then.

510
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:07,640
"My boyfriend is Yang Hyun Bin,
not Park Jun Hyeok!"

511
00:30:07,710 --> 00:30:09,280
Why can't you just say that?

512
00:30:10,550 --> 00:30:14,050
- Are you jealous right now?
- Of course, I'm jealous!

513
00:30:15,550 --> 00:30:19,590
I wasn't jealous when they mistook
the VP for your girlfriend.

514
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:23,460
Why not?
How could you not be jealous?

515
00:30:23,890 --> 00:30:26,030
- It didn't upset you?
- Not at all.

516
00:30:26,100 --> 00:30:30,330
It bothers me. When Dr. Han arrives,
I'll tell her everything.

517
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:34,740
I'm going to proudly announce
that I'm your boyfriend, not him.

518
00:30:35,170 --> 00:30:39,310
- No. Absolutely not.
- Why not? Our parents just made up.

519
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:42,380
That's exactly why you can't.
If they find out about us now,

520
00:30:42,450 --> 00:30:44,510
their relationship might go south
all over again.

521
00:30:45,620 --> 00:30:50,220
I'll find the right time.
So don't you say a word.

522
00:30:50,290 --> 00:30:51,320
Got it?

523
00:30:53,660 --> 00:30:54,720
Yang Hyun Bin.

524
00:30:56,090 --> 00:31:00,160
Don't say my full name like that.
You're scaring me.

525
00:31:00,660 --> 00:31:02,170
I'm telling you, don't do it.

526
00:31:05,240 --> 00:31:07,240
You're going to pay for this,
Park Jun Hyeok. Darn it.

527
00:31:07,670 --> 00:31:10,610
How dare he be treated as
the future son-in-law instead of me?

528
00:31:11,270 --> 00:31:12,440
I'm going to destroy him.

529
00:31:19,080 --> 00:31:21,220
What's wrong?
You have a bug in your ear?

530
00:31:21,450 --> 00:31:23,320
Gosh, my ears are burning.
Who's bad-mouthing me?

531
00:31:23,620 --> 00:31:26,920
- Was it you?
- No. Why blame me?

532
00:31:27,490 --> 00:31:28,630
My gosh...

533
00:31:42,070 --> 00:31:44,070
Here are the concept drafts
for the upcoming photo shoot.

534
00:31:44,540 --> 00:31:46,940
We'll make the final decision
after today's fitting.

535
00:31:47,210 --> 00:31:51,410
The shoot will be in the studio,
and we'll shoot that outfit first.

536
00:31:52,320 --> 00:31:57,020
It's my first shoot like this,
so I'm worried about my posing.

537
00:31:57,650 --> 00:31:59,290
You don't have to worry
about that at all.

538
00:31:59,520 --> 00:32:02,990
We'll have a board on set
with sample poses and expressions,

539
00:32:03,090 --> 00:32:05,660
so if you're not sure what to do,
you can just take a look.

540
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:09,930
Thank you, Jun Hyeok.
That puts my mind at ease.

541
00:32:13,770 --> 00:32:16,440
Doctor, the outfits
for your fitting are all ready.

542
00:32:17,770 --> 00:32:19,980
- Should I go get changed?
- Yes.

543
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:28,380
The length and the fit are
absolutely perfect on you.

544
00:32:29,550 --> 00:32:31,890
I'm not sure if it really suits me.

545
00:32:32,390 --> 00:32:35,630
My gosh. It's a modern style,
so it's perfect for you, Doctor.

546
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:37,160
You think so?

547
00:32:37,890 --> 00:32:40,360
All right!
Have some snacks while you work.

548
00:32:43,270 --> 00:32:46,940
Our clothes look even better
on you, Doctor.

549
00:32:48,140 --> 00:32:53,110
If so, that's a credit
to the talented designers.

550
00:32:59,580 --> 00:33:00,620
All right, everyone!

551
00:33:00,850 --> 00:33:05,520
I have good news. And I'm so happy
to share it with Dr. Han here.

552
00:33:05,620 --> 00:33:08,390
- I couldn't be happier.
- Oh, are the contest results out?

553
00:33:08,790 --> 00:33:09,960
We won, didn't we?

554
00:33:10,460 --> 00:33:11,460
What?

555
00:33:12,130 --> 00:33:14,160
Well... Yes!

556
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:20,570
Everyone worked so hard,
and the results are...

557
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:22,710
Director! Congratulations!

558
00:33:24,970 --> 00:33:26,610
Why did he have to
cut me off like that?

559
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:29,210
I hardly did any of the work...

560
00:33:29,280 --> 00:33:32,780
- Yes! Everyone worked so hard!
- Great work.

561
00:33:35,250 --> 00:33:36,950
Congratulations, everyone.

562
00:33:37,390 --> 00:33:39,720
I'm so glad I could be here
to hear the good news with you all.

563
00:33:40,620 --> 00:33:43,130
You really worked so hard,
Jun Hyeok.

564
00:33:44,030 --> 00:33:45,030
Thank you.

565
00:33:46,930 --> 00:33:49,570
Director!
This is all thanks to you, Director.

566
00:33:49,870 --> 00:33:50,870
Thank you!

567
00:33:51,770 --> 00:33:54,840
- You worked so hard, Director.
- Thank you.

568
00:33:55,640 --> 00:33:57,470
Oh, no, it was nothing.

569
00:33:57,540 --> 00:34:00,110
Hey! Let's go out to celebrate.
Doctor, you should come with us.

570
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:02,250
- What? What do you guys think?
- I'm in!

571
00:34:02,310 --> 00:34:05,620
- Let's party!
- Party!

572
00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:09,750
- Party!
- Party!

573
00:34:09,820 --> 00:34:12,020
- Party!
- Party!

574
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:18,930
So, we won't need traffic control
for the shoot?

575
00:34:19,460 --> 00:34:24,100
No. We'll mostly be filming
inside and around the clinics.

576
00:34:24,700 --> 00:34:27,870
The film crew isn't that big either,
so there's no need to worry.

577
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:31,070
Still, a crowd might gather
to watch the shoot.

578
00:34:31,140 --> 00:34:33,180
You never know what might happen,

579
00:34:33,710 --> 00:34:35,880
so Officer Jung should stand by
at the clinic.

580
00:34:36,250 --> 00:34:38,680
Pardon? Right, yes, sir.

581
00:34:39,220 --> 00:34:40,750
We'd really appreciate that.

582
00:34:41,680 --> 00:34:43,590
It's for Onjeong,
so it's the least I can do.

583
00:34:44,490 --> 00:34:46,690
- By the way, Chief.
- Yes?

584
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:49,230
We should tell the doctors
about that thing.

585
00:34:49,690 --> 00:34:52,730
- Oh, that's right.
- What? What are you talking about?

586
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:54,930
There was a criminal case...

587
00:34:54,930 --> 00:34:56,900
at the intersection
by the health center.

588
00:34:57,330 --> 00:34:58,370
What?

589
00:34:58,430 --> 00:35:01,570
Someone broke into a clothing store
when the owner was there alone...

590
00:35:01,640 --> 00:35:04,210
and tried to rob her
before running away.

591
00:35:04,810 --> 00:35:08,010
What?
Who would dare do that in Onjeong?

592
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:11,310
Wait, if they fled,
are they still at large?

593
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:13,750
Yes, we're tracking the suspect.

594
00:35:14,150 --> 00:35:17,990
We'll be patrolling more, so please
report anyone who looks suspicious.

595
00:35:18,350 --> 00:35:20,860
And especially for those
who run their businesses alone,

596
00:35:21,090 --> 00:35:24,090
please advise them
not to be alone late at night.

597
00:35:24,430 --> 00:35:26,830
Please tell everyone
to look out for each other.

598
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:31,200
Yes, got it. I'll tell
the Merchants' Association.

599
00:35:31,300 --> 00:35:32,970
- Yes.
- My goodness.

600
00:35:33,240 --> 00:35:37,010
(Onjeong Market,
Merchants' Association)

601
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:40,180
- Then, good luck with the shoot.
- Yes, we appreciate the help.

602
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:42,040
- Yes, thank you.
- Take care.

603
00:35:42,110 --> 00:35:43,780
- We'll get going then.
- Okay.

604
00:35:44,810 --> 00:35:46,180
- Hey, Jeong Han.
- Yes?

605
00:35:46,180 --> 00:35:48,320
If you have time, do you want me
to give you some acupressure?

606
00:35:48,380 --> 00:35:51,150
Acupressure? What?
But I have an appointment.

607
00:35:51,250 --> 00:35:53,160
- Hey, stand still.
- Okay.

608
00:35:53,260 --> 00:35:56,530
The hollow under your cheekbone
is an acupressure point.

609
00:35:56,530 --> 00:35:58,900
If you press here gently like this,

610
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:02,160
it helps blood circulation
and improves your complexion.

611
00:36:02,270 --> 00:36:04,000
Really? Right here?

612
00:36:04,070 --> 00:36:08,040
Yes. And if you press here
in the center of your philtrum,

613
00:36:08,340 --> 00:36:12,170
it'll also reduce facial puffiness.
Press it gently now and then, okay?

614
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:15,980
So that handsome face of yours
looks even better on camera.

615
00:36:16,150 --> 00:36:19,780
Fine. I'll drop by when I have time,
so you can do it for me, all right?

616
00:36:19,980 --> 00:36:22,350
- Hey, we'll be late. Let's go.
- Jeong Han.

617
00:36:22,920 --> 00:36:25,250
Don't get the wrong idea,
but just hear me out.

618
00:36:25,690 --> 00:36:28,720
- What is it?
- It's about Councilor Hwang.

619
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:31,890
He'd like to be on our show.

620
00:36:32,500 --> 00:36:33,560
Oh, really?

621
00:36:34,230 --> 00:36:36,630
Yes, it'd be helpful for him
in many ways.

622
00:36:36,900 --> 00:36:38,900
The thing is,
he wants it to seem natural,

623
00:36:39,070 --> 00:36:41,970
as if we're all close friends.

624
00:36:43,140 --> 00:36:47,140
So for that to work,
let's eat together before the show.

625
00:36:52,010 --> 00:36:56,220
- Okay, I'll get in touch with him.
- Really? You'd do that?

626
00:36:56,290 --> 00:36:58,390
Of course. You worry too much.

627
00:36:58,820 --> 00:37:01,020
- Man, thanks.
- Hey, it's nothing.

628
00:37:02,660 --> 00:37:04,290
My gosh! Seriously?

629
00:37:04,790 --> 00:37:07,930
Dr. Gong is arranging a meeting
with Councilor Hwang himself?

630
00:37:10,530 --> 00:37:13,740
I'm so happy
that you're happy, honey.

631
00:37:14,740 --> 00:37:17,670
Yes. I just got
to Hyun Bin's company.

632
00:37:18,370 --> 00:37:19,380
Okay.

633
00:37:24,450 --> 00:37:28,420
- My goodness, Doctor!
- Fancy meeting you here.

634
00:37:29,550 --> 00:37:30,690
What brings you here?

635
00:37:30,950 --> 00:37:33,420
I'm here for a photo shoot.

636
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:35,060
That's right.

637
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:37,360
You're the exclusive model
for this brand.

638
00:37:37,630 --> 00:37:39,500
You're so cool.

639
00:37:40,760 --> 00:37:44,700
- But wait, what is all this?
- Oh, this.

640
00:37:45,100 --> 00:37:48,500
After what you told me, Doctor,
I had to do something.

641
00:37:49,210 --> 00:37:50,210
Pardon?

642
00:37:50,470 --> 00:37:52,070
It's ginseng chicken soup.

643
00:37:52,410 --> 00:37:55,210
I put in a lot of abalone
and made it with the utmost care.

644
00:37:55,750 --> 00:37:59,880
I was going to ask the VP
to take it to the Chairman.

645
00:38:00,150 --> 00:38:02,820
I don't know
if this is a good idea...

646
00:38:03,120 --> 00:38:04,120
Why?

647
00:38:04,650 --> 00:38:06,990
The VP was a huge help to Hyun Bin
when he was studying abroad.

648
00:38:07,060 --> 00:38:11,560
Can't I say this is
just to show my gratitude?

649
00:38:12,090 --> 00:38:13,830
I understand
where you're coming from,

650
00:38:13,830 --> 00:38:16,470
but they're not that close yet,
so it's a bit...

651
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:18,970
Don't you think this might be
putting too much pressure on them?

652
00:38:23,970 --> 00:38:27,980
- You think so?
- Yes. Rushing it will ruin things.

653
00:38:28,510 --> 00:38:30,450
Don't rush. Take it slow and steady.

654
00:38:32,350 --> 00:38:34,750
I did go back and forth on it a lot.

655
00:38:35,790 --> 00:38:37,990
I got ahead of myself
and almost made a mistake.

656
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:41,260
Running into you here
was a real stroke of luck, Doctor.

657
00:38:41,490 --> 00:38:44,960
Gosh, but you made it from scratch.
What will you do with it?

658
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:49,230
It's fine. I made some for Hyun Bin,
and I was on my way to his place.

659
00:38:49,370 --> 00:38:50,600
I'll just leave this there with his.

660
00:38:51,500 --> 00:38:53,670
Thank you so much, Doctor.

661
00:39:03,010 --> 00:39:04,010
What gives?

662
00:39:04,950 --> 00:39:06,720
She left for the day
without even stopping by.

663
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:09,950
I'm in a bad mood,
and she didn't try to cheer me up.

664
00:39:11,590 --> 00:39:13,820
The least she could do was
take me to that Argentinian place.

665
00:39:14,590 --> 00:39:15,590
That's cold.

666
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:23,370
Hello?

667
00:39:24,530 --> 00:39:25,530
Your text?

668
00:39:26,900 --> 00:39:29,110
I'm sorry. I was in a meeting,
so I didn't see your text.

669
00:39:30,440 --> 00:39:33,480
The thing is,
I made some ginseng chicken soup.

670
00:39:33,740 --> 00:39:34,740
Ginseng chicken soup?

671
00:39:34,980 --> 00:39:39,080
Yes. I was in the neighborhood,
so I've been waiting to drop it off.

672
00:39:39,450 --> 00:39:42,850
Would it be okay
if I could get the passcode?

673
00:39:43,550 --> 00:39:47,160
Of course. I'll text you the code,
so you can wait inside.

674
00:39:47,490 --> 00:39:50,290
I'm almost done. I'll be there soon.
We can eat together.

675
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:52,360
Really? That sounds lovely.

676
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:54,730
Don't rush.
Take your time getting here.

677
00:39:55,700 --> 00:39:58,600
Okay, wait for me inside.
I have something to tell you, too.

678
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:31,630
No way.
He used my birthday for the code.

679
00:40:37,310 --> 00:40:40,240
All right!
Gong Ju Ah, you culinary genius.

680
00:40:40,710 --> 00:40:44,580
I'll make an Argentinian meal
and cheer him right up.

681
00:40:46,420 --> 00:40:48,280
Okay, first things first...

682
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:55,020
Meat, breadcrumbs, and...

683
00:40:56,260 --> 00:40:59,560
I got the ingredients for milanesa,
and next...

684
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:02,770
Parsley, oregano,

685
00:41:03,430 --> 00:41:04,430
and garlic.

686
00:41:06,570 --> 00:41:09,940
Oh! Shoot,
I forgot the red wine vinegar.

687
00:41:10,510 --> 00:41:12,780
I heard it's what gives chimichurri
its kick.

688
00:41:14,040 --> 00:41:16,750
Gosh, I'd better run out and get it.

689
00:41:50,280 --> 00:41:52,720
It was the unit at the very end,
right?

690
00:41:58,620 --> 00:42:01,290
Didn't he say
to press the star key first?

691
00:42:02,290 --> 00:42:03,290
Or was it the pound key?

692
00:42:07,030 --> 00:42:08,030
Oh, no.

693
00:42:10,970 --> 00:42:12,300
The star is last.

694
00:42:16,340 --> 00:42:17,940
There we go.

695
00:42:29,150 --> 00:42:31,450
I'll put the ginseng chicken soup
here.

696
00:42:34,160 --> 00:42:37,890
But this is what I really came for.

697
00:42:39,190 --> 00:42:42,130
Gosh, I can't believe how much
I paid for this paper talisman.

698
00:42:42,970 --> 00:42:43,970
- Talisman?
- Dear Shaman.

699
00:42:44,470 --> 00:42:45,630
Please let my dear Hyun Bin...

700
00:42:46,070 --> 00:42:49,440
win over the Vice President
for good.

701
00:42:51,670 --> 00:42:54,480
This goes under his pillow, right?

702
00:43:18,300 --> 00:43:20,170
Oh, right.
I should wash my hands first.

703
00:43:24,510 --> 00:43:26,310
Oh, what is this?

704
00:43:35,620 --> 00:43:37,290
Why is there a woman's hair here?

705
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:43,430
Does the Vice President come over?

706
00:43:44,160 --> 00:43:48,100
No, that can't be it.
She has short hair.

707
00:43:48,530 --> 00:43:50,470
Then what's this?
Did one of my hairs fall out?

708
00:43:53,000 --> 00:43:54,270
Hyun Bin.

709
00:43:55,570 --> 00:43:56,570
You're here.

710
00:43:57,770 --> 00:44:01,910
Goodness, I told you not to rush.
What are you doing here so soon?

711
00:44:02,110 --> 00:44:05,650
Your text was from two hours ago.
Where have you been waiting?

712
00:44:06,420 --> 00:44:10,490
- The parking lot, inside my car.
- You could've left it at security.

713
00:44:10,620 --> 00:44:12,220
I didn't know
when you'd be getting off work.

714
00:44:12,490 --> 00:44:15,790
I was worried it would go bad,
so I wanted to put it in the fridge.

715
00:44:15,960 --> 00:44:18,860
Next time, it's really okay.
You can just call me directly.

716
00:44:19,030 --> 00:44:21,030
I couldn't possibly bother you
while you're working.

717
00:44:22,100 --> 00:44:24,570
I'll heat the ginseng chicken soup.
You go get changed and wash up.

718
00:44:24,630 --> 00:44:27,500
- Okay.
- Oh, right. What was it?

719
00:44:27,840 --> 00:44:28,840
Oh, right.

720
00:44:29,200 --> 00:44:33,180
So many people are doing
the video challenge imitating you.

721
00:44:33,280 --> 00:44:36,750
Really? That's wonderful.
This is a good thing, right?

722
00:44:37,010 --> 00:44:39,080
Of course, it is.
Thank you for your consent.

723
00:44:40,220 --> 00:44:41,720
I'm inside your apartment right now.

724
00:44:42,250 --> 00:44:44,320
Please,
can you just get her to leave?

725
00:44:46,690 --> 00:44:50,890
I'm just so happy these days.
Your father is so happy, too.

726
00:44:51,890 --> 00:44:53,330
That's all thanks to you.

727
00:44:53,800 --> 00:44:56,800
Right? I guess posting my fall video
was a really good idea after all.

728
00:45:00,700 --> 00:45:01,800
(Director Yang Hyun Bin)

729
00:45:05,810 --> 00:45:07,280
What did you just say?

730
00:45:12,950 --> 00:45:13,980
What have I done?

731
00:45:15,080 --> 00:45:16,620
Oh, no. I must be out of my mind.

732
00:45:18,150 --> 00:45:19,150
So...

733
00:45:20,060 --> 00:45:21,060
that video...

734
00:45:22,020 --> 00:45:24,630
You're the one who uploaded it?

735
00:45:27,560 --> 00:45:28,560
Well...

736
00:45:29,700 --> 00:45:30,700
Well, Hyun Bin...

737
00:45:31,630 --> 00:45:34,100
The thing is...
What am I going to do?

738
00:45:34,800 --> 00:45:36,840
Why can't I think of
a single excuse?

739
00:45:38,170 --> 00:45:39,340
Dad's home, isn't he?

740
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:43,150
Hyun Bin. Just talk to me. Please?

741
00:45:44,350 --> 00:45:47,250
Hyun Bin. Oh, no!
What do I do, really?

742
00:45:48,450 --> 00:45:49,450
Hyun Bin.

743
00:45:50,090 --> 00:45:51,790
Hyun Bin, what am I going to do?

744
00:46:11,110 --> 00:46:13,780
Oh, no. Hyun Bin, wait.

745
00:46:13,840 --> 00:46:16,180
Where's the car parked?
Give me the keys. I'm driving.

746
00:46:16,250 --> 00:46:17,250
Hyun Bin.

747
00:46:17,510 --> 00:46:20,080
I did it. It was me.
Just talk to me. Please?

748
00:46:24,020 --> 00:46:26,960
Hey, Eun Bin, it's me.
Are you home? Have you eaten?

749
00:46:27,620 --> 00:46:30,360
Really?
Then can you do me a quick favor?

750
00:46:33,000 --> 00:46:34,960
(Nurse Oh Jin Ah)

751
00:46:35,560 --> 00:46:36,600
Oh, gosh.

752
00:46:37,470 --> 00:46:39,400
- Hello.
- Hello.

753
00:46:39,470 --> 00:46:40,470
I hope your treatment goes well.

754
00:46:41,200 --> 00:46:43,270
Goodness. You're here again.

755
00:46:43,570 --> 00:46:45,240
Are you Dr. Gong's lover
or something now?

756
00:46:45,640 --> 00:46:47,680
No, we were just going to play
a game of pool.

757
00:46:48,540 --> 00:46:49,780
When does the late shift end?

758
00:46:50,480 --> 00:46:52,250
It's still going to be a while.

759
00:46:52,410 --> 00:46:54,850
- At 10 p.m.
- Really?

760
00:47:00,060 --> 00:47:01,060
Hyun Bin. What's up?

761
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:03,160
Right now?

762
00:47:04,460 --> 00:47:05,460
All right.

763
00:47:08,300 --> 00:47:10,130
- Just a moment.
- And you're feeling some pain?

764
00:47:10,200 --> 00:47:11,770
- Yes.
- Oh, dear.

765
00:47:12,230 --> 00:47:14,900
- It hurts here and here, right?
- Yes.

766
00:47:14,970 --> 00:47:16,840
You have fluid buildup here, too.
See?

767
00:47:18,070 --> 00:47:19,940
You really need to rest.

768
00:47:20,310 --> 00:47:22,380
- But you haven't been able to rest.
- I know. I can't afford to.

769
00:47:22,510 --> 00:47:25,910
- All right. I'll drain the fluid.
- Okay.

770
00:47:25,980 --> 00:47:27,450
Let me give you
some emergency treatment.

771
00:47:27,750 --> 00:47:30,390
How could you be so despicable,
Father?

772
00:47:33,020 --> 00:47:35,020
How could you? How?

773
00:47:35,560 --> 00:47:37,590
Hey, it's just...

774
00:47:38,260 --> 00:47:39,260
Hyun Bin.

775
00:47:39,760 --> 00:47:41,400
Your father has done nothing wrong.

776
00:47:41,700 --> 00:47:44,000
I'm the one who did it.
It was all my fault.

777
00:47:44,230 --> 00:47:46,440
So please, don't blame your father.
Okay?

778
00:47:46,870 --> 00:47:48,500
She only did it because of you,
Father.

779
00:47:49,170 --> 00:47:50,440
Because of your greed,

780
00:47:50,810 --> 00:47:52,940
my stepmother was forced
to humiliate herself.

781
00:47:54,010 --> 00:47:55,410
How could you just stand by
and watch?

782
00:47:56,080 --> 00:47:58,510
- How could you?
- Hyun Bin.

783
00:47:59,010 --> 00:48:00,050
You, Father...

784
00:48:01,380 --> 00:48:02,950
You still don't know
the first thing about love.

785
00:48:04,250 --> 00:48:07,060
You were always so cold
to my birth mother.

786
00:48:08,060 --> 00:48:09,660
How lonely she was,

787
00:48:10,330 --> 00:48:12,860
and how she craved your affection...
I remember it all.

788
00:48:13,260 --> 00:48:14,260
And that's why...

789
00:48:14,900 --> 00:48:16,270
I could understand Mom,
why she wasn't able...

790
00:48:16,270 --> 00:48:17,370
to show her love for Eun Bin and me,

791
00:48:18,070 --> 00:48:20,140
and why she ended up leaving you
for another man.

792
00:48:20,840 --> 00:48:22,040
I came to understand her completely.

793
00:48:23,440 --> 00:48:25,610
And yet, you refused to admit
your own faults.

794
00:48:26,010 --> 00:48:27,480
You just blamed her for leaving,

795
00:48:28,110 --> 00:48:29,650
and you lived your life
suspecting my stepmother.

796
00:48:30,180 --> 00:48:31,510
And now, you're using her?

797
00:48:32,080 --> 00:48:33,080
You little punk.

798
00:48:33,350 --> 00:48:35,680
- What do you mean, using her?
- Honey, please stop.

799
00:48:36,080 --> 00:48:39,490
If you love her, protect her
from being hurt or in pain.

800
00:48:40,090 --> 00:48:41,720
Isn't that what a husband
is supposed to do?

801
00:48:45,260 --> 00:48:46,500
Did you thank her?

802
00:48:47,100 --> 00:48:48,660
Did you tell her she did a good job?

803
00:48:49,130 --> 00:48:52,530
Were you happy you got your way,
thanks to her being humiliated?

804
00:48:52,730 --> 00:48:57,270
Hyun Bin, don't overreact.
Honey, say something.

805
00:48:58,970 --> 00:48:59,980
I...

806
00:49:01,180 --> 00:49:02,180
I was wrong.

807
00:49:02,510 --> 00:49:05,450
And you're just realizing that now?

808
00:49:05,780 --> 00:49:08,080
You should've thought of that
before you acted!

809
00:49:11,890 --> 00:49:12,890
You know...

810
00:49:13,590 --> 00:49:15,690
what Gong Ju Ah had to endure
because of that, right?

811
00:49:16,090 --> 00:49:18,460
I was ignorant.

812
00:49:18,930 --> 00:49:21,600
I was so stupid.
I'm so sorry, Hyun Bin.

813
00:49:21,800 --> 00:49:25,470
We really had no idea
it would blow up like this.

814
00:49:26,470 --> 00:49:29,070
Saying you didn't know
doesn't absolve you of blame.

815
00:49:29,940 --> 00:49:32,510
Even if you didn't intend
to hurt anyone,

816
00:49:33,110 --> 00:49:35,580
there are some lines
you just don't cross.

817
00:49:36,140 --> 00:49:39,310
That's why I showed up
at the disciplinary hearing.

818
00:49:40,150 --> 00:49:41,420
And I cleaned up the mess.

819
00:49:41,850 --> 00:49:42,850
You see, I...

820
00:49:43,120 --> 00:49:46,090
I thought it was an act of goodwill.

821
00:49:47,420 --> 00:49:49,790
And Dr. Gong's family
probably thought so too.

822
00:49:50,790 --> 00:49:51,790
But still...

823
00:49:52,230 --> 00:49:55,030
In the end, it all worked out
for the best, right?

824
00:49:56,730 --> 00:50:00,570
Go tell them the truth.
And give them a proper apology.

825
00:50:01,870 --> 00:50:05,870
- Hyun Bin.
- If you try to cover this up,

826
00:50:07,710 --> 00:50:09,410
then don't ever expect
to see me again.

827
00:50:13,250 --> 00:50:14,250
Hyun Bin.

828
00:50:15,550 --> 00:50:16,550
It's just that...

829
00:50:20,060 --> 00:50:23,160
Hyun Bin, wait a second. Hyun Bin!

830
00:50:29,300 --> 00:50:33,740
Hey, Hyun Bin.
Please, just talk to me, okay?

831
00:50:34,170 --> 00:50:36,970
It wasn't your father.
I wanted to do it.

832
00:50:37,410 --> 00:50:40,340
I'll tell them everything
and apologize. So please...

833
00:50:40,810 --> 00:50:42,910
So please, don't be so hard
on your father, okay?

834
00:50:43,110 --> 00:50:46,420
You're a wise woman.
You can make your own judgments.

835
00:50:47,780 --> 00:50:49,350
Don't get so used to
my father's ambition...

836
00:50:49,850 --> 00:50:51,920
that you keep making
these wrong choices.

837
00:50:53,490 --> 00:50:54,560
I'm...

838
00:50:55,860 --> 00:50:57,690
I'm so ashamed,
I have no idea what to say.

839
00:50:58,690 --> 00:50:59,900
I'm not blameless either.

840
00:51:00,600 --> 00:51:02,730
I used your video for marketing.

841
00:51:03,830 --> 00:51:05,800
So in a way, I used you too.

842
00:51:06,070 --> 00:51:08,700
No. How is that using me?

843
00:51:09,570 --> 00:51:12,870
I was just so happy
I could help our family.

844
00:51:13,740 --> 00:51:16,480
You don't have to do anything.
That's what family is.

845
00:51:17,110 --> 00:51:20,580
Don't feel like
you have to prove your worth.

846
00:51:21,380 --> 00:51:23,890
Just having you here
is more than enough.

847
00:51:25,090 --> 00:51:28,520
You don't have to be your best.
It's okay not to be perfect.

848
00:51:28,590 --> 00:51:30,730
Eat all the delicious food you want.
It's fine if you gain weight.

849
00:51:30,930 --> 00:51:33,700
We'll love you all the same.

850
00:51:39,230 --> 00:51:40,240
Okay.

851
00:51:41,240 --> 00:51:42,740
I know what you mean.

852
00:51:44,070 --> 00:51:45,070
But...

853
00:51:47,510 --> 00:51:49,580
But listen, Hyun Bin.

854
00:51:51,310 --> 00:51:52,310
I'm asking you for a favor.

855
00:51:53,720 --> 00:51:54,980
You saw it for yourself.

856
00:51:55,650 --> 00:51:57,790
The two families are finally
getting along now.

857
00:51:58,650 --> 00:51:59,690
Right?

858
00:52:02,520 --> 00:52:03,590
Let's not say anything.

859
00:52:04,560 --> 00:52:05,590
I'm begging you.

860
00:52:06,860 --> 00:52:08,230
And for Ju Ah's sake,

861
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:10,670
what good would come
from her knowing?

862
00:52:13,370 --> 00:52:14,540
Hyun Bin, please.

863
00:52:23,550 --> 00:52:24,550
Hold on a second.

864
00:52:31,050 --> 00:52:34,090
You see, I'm not much of a writer,

865
00:52:34,560 --> 00:52:36,260
so I figured it'd be better
to say it in person.

866
00:52:36,630 --> 00:52:38,530
What if this was all staged?

867
00:52:38,930 --> 00:52:41,730
Mom, you're saying crazy things.

868
00:52:42,700 --> 00:52:47,370
Seriously, who would post
a video of themselves falling?

869
00:52:51,210 --> 00:52:52,810
Turns out Mom was right.

870
00:53:02,080 --> 00:53:03,720
Can you come out for a minute?

871
00:53:22,770 --> 00:53:24,170
I'm sorry, honey.

872
00:53:25,110 --> 00:53:27,210
I kept telling you not to slip up,

873
00:53:27,840 --> 00:53:29,110
and yet I ended up blurting it out.

874
00:53:30,610 --> 00:53:31,610
No.

875
00:53:32,910 --> 00:53:35,320
It's a mistake anyone would've made.

876
00:53:36,250 --> 00:53:37,250
Hyun Bin...

877
00:53:38,790 --> 00:53:41,020
I think he's going to tell
Gong Ju Ah, honey.

878
00:53:47,160 --> 00:53:49,330
Why? Are you going somewhere?

879
00:53:51,030 --> 00:53:52,870
I have to be the one
to tell Jeong Han.

880
00:53:53,640 --> 00:53:55,500
Let me go.
I'll go to their house and...

881
00:53:55,500 --> 00:53:56,740
No, Se Ri.

882
00:53:57,340 --> 00:53:59,140
I'll take care of this.

883
00:53:59,980 --> 00:54:01,710
Hyun Bin wasn't wrong
about a single thing.

884
00:54:02,510 --> 00:54:05,350
I'm the one who put you up to this.
I should have stopped you.

885
00:54:06,580 --> 00:54:07,980
From now on, don't do anything.

886
00:54:08,650 --> 00:54:10,720
Don't do anything for my sake.

887
00:54:12,090 --> 00:54:13,090
Honey.

888
00:54:14,190 --> 00:54:15,190
But still...

889
00:54:16,260 --> 00:54:17,430
I love you.

890
00:54:18,690 --> 00:54:20,900
It's not that I love you
because you love me.

891
00:54:21,960 --> 00:54:23,630
I love you, and I trust you.

892
00:54:26,100 --> 00:54:27,270
Okay, Se Ri?

893
00:54:29,240 --> 00:54:30,340
Honey...

894
00:54:48,790 --> 00:54:51,330
There's something
I have to tell you.

895
00:54:52,090 --> 00:54:54,800
I couldn't let tonight pass
without saying it.

896
00:55:05,910 --> 00:55:09,380
I showed up out of the blue
all the way in Onjeong at this hour,

897
00:55:09,980 --> 00:55:11,050
but you don't seem surprised.

898
00:55:12,010 --> 00:55:13,520
I just thought it was very you.

899
00:55:14,380 --> 00:55:16,450
I figured you wouldn't hide it.

900
00:55:21,690 --> 00:55:24,660
I just came from your apartment.

901
00:55:26,230 --> 00:55:27,600
I was there earlier.

902
00:55:32,000 --> 00:55:33,770
I was going to make you
some Argentinian food.

903
00:55:34,200 --> 00:55:36,970
I was waiting
to surprise you with it,

904
00:55:37,840 --> 00:55:40,710
but then your mother
came in, so I hid.

905
00:55:48,120 --> 00:55:49,180
So that's what happened.

906
00:55:50,390 --> 00:55:51,390
So?

907
00:55:52,720 --> 00:55:53,760
You heard everything?

908
00:55:55,660 --> 00:55:56,660
Yes.

909
00:56:01,230 --> 00:56:03,630
I thought
I had figured out what to say.

910
00:56:05,770 --> 00:56:06,770
But it's...

911
00:56:07,400 --> 00:56:08,770
hard to get the words out.

912
00:56:10,940 --> 00:56:12,410
Don't apologize for them.

913
00:56:13,840 --> 00:56:15,810
You didn't do anything wrong.

914
00:56:17,150 --> 00:56:20,150
I'm not going to ask you
to understand or forgive.

915
00:56:20,450 --> 00:56:21,780
That would be too selfish.

916
00:56:23,490 --> 00:56:24,550
It's just...

917
00:56:25,720 --> 00:56:29,420
I feel bad that you're not the type
to hide something like this.

918
00:56:32,060 --> 00:56:35,530
As their son, I was torn between
being angry at my parents...

919
00:56:36,430 --> 00:56:39,030
and wanting to protect them.
That's true.

920
00:56:40,100 --> 00:56:41,770
But if I were to hide what happened,

921
00:56:42,340 --> 00:56:44,170
I'd be just as guilty as they are.

922
00:56:44,940 --> 00:56:46,040
And that...

923
00:56:47,580 --> 00:56:49,780
wouldn't be the Yang Hyun Bin
that you fell for.

924
00:56:51,010 --> 00:56:52,010
Right?

925
00:56:57,520 --> 00:57:00,660
I guess I was a little arrogant.

926
00:57:01,590 --> 00:57:02,620
To believe...

927
00:57:03,890 --> 00:57:06,130
that I could change my family.

928
00:57:09,800 --> 00:57:11,430
Throughout this whole ordeal,

929
00:57:12,370 --> 00:57:14,240
I was right there by your side.

930
00:57:15,370 --> 00:57:17,470
And the fact that
I still couldn't protect you...

931
00:57:18,570 --> 00:57:19,740
I'm so sorry.

932
00:57:22,880 --> 00:57:23,910
I think I have to...

933
00:57:24,810 --> 00:57:26,950
leave everything up to you now.

934
00:57:29,620 --> 00:57:31,920
It's a shock to realize
that my love for you...

935
00:57:33,420 --> 00:57:36,930
could be what hurts you, but...

936
00:57:38,190 --> 00:57:39,690
what's even more devastating...

937
00:57:41,430 --> 00:57:43,060
is that I can't promise you...

938
00:57:43,460 --> 00:57:45,330
something like this
won't happen again.

939
00:57:48,870 --> 00:57:49,870
Can you give me...

940
00:57:52,040 --> 00:57:53,440
some time...

941
00:57:54,240 --> 00:57:56,240
to think about it?

942
00:58:11,760 --> 00:58:13,190
I'm so sorry, Jeong Han.

943
00:58:14,230 --> 00:58:15,960
What I did was unforgivable.

944
00:58:16,870 --> 00:58:19,500
We really didn't mean
for this to happen.

945
00:58:19,970 --> 00:58:21,940
No, we did. We knew.

946
00:58:22,470 --> 00:58:25,170
No, that's not what we meant...

947
00:58:25,840 --> 00:58:28,640
What we intended to...

948
00:58:31,050 --> 00:58:32,210
Why can't I get this right?

949
00:58:34,620 --> 00:58:35,650
So...

950
00:58:36,220 --> 00:58:38,250
- Jeong Han.
- Yes? What's up?

951
00:58:38,320 --> 00:58:39,390
You scared me.

952
00:58:40,390 --> 00:58:42,060
Where did you come from?
Do you teleport or something?

953
00:58:42,990 --> 00:58:46,090
You were too busy muttering
to yourself to notice me.

954
00:58:46,530 --> 00:58:49,960
What's up?
You sounded weird on the phone.

955
00:58:50,100 --> 00:58:53,370
I had Nurse Oh close up
and rushed right over.

956
00:58:54,000 --> 00:58:55,640
It's...

957
00:58:57,040 --> 00:58:58,940
What? What is it?

958
00:58:59,810 --> 00:59:01,180
Not here.

959
00:59:01,680 --> 00:59:03,180
Let's go somewhere we can talk.

960
00:59:04,280 --> 00:59:06,480
- Go where? Goodness.
- Let's just...

961
00:59:11,520 --> 00:59:12,520
Se Ri.

962
00:59:13,660 --> 00:59:14,660
Yes?

963
00:59:16,460 --> 00:59:18,730
Se Ri, is something wrong?

964
00:59:19,790 --> 00:59:21,230
No, nothing's wrong at all.

965
00:59:21,560 --> 00:59:24,430
Come on. Hyun Bin randomly told us
to take Grandpa...

966
00:59:24,500 --> 00:59:26,670
out to dinner.
There has to be a reason.

967
00:59:26,730 --> 00:59:30,310
I know. But where's Hyun Bin?
And my brother isn't here either.

968
00:59:30,840 --> 00:59:34,040
- Excuse me, I'm just stepping out.
- Gosh, Se Ri.

969
00:59:34,310 --> 00:59:36,950
No, you can't go out alone so late.
Haven't you heard what happened?

970
00:59:38,050 --> 00:59:39,910
What happened, Auntie?

971
00:59:40,420 --> 00:59:43,750
Yesterday, a robber held up a shop
where a lone woman was working.

972
00:59:43,790 --> 00:59:47,060
- And they still haven't caught him.
- Gosh, really?

973
00:59:55,400 --> 00:59:57,300
Don't tell me you sleep here.

974
00:59:57,530 --> 00:59:59,230
Yes. I sleep here.

975
01:00:10,880 --> 01:00:13,580
You don't think
he'll return tonight, do you?

976
01:00:14,780 --> 01:00:18,020
It was only an attempted robbery.
He could try again.

977
01:00:42,640 --> 01:00:43,810
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

978
01:00:55,560 --> 01:00:58,430
Okay. Finished closing out.

979
01:00:59,330 --> 01:01:00,330
Done.

980
01:01:08,770 --> 01:01:11,010
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

981
01:01:11,070 --> 01:01:12,770
(Reception)

982
01:01:23,790 --> 01:01:24,890
May I help you?

983
01:01:25,520 --> 01:01:27,420
We're closed for the day.

984
01:01:39,370 --> 01:01:42,100
(Police)

985
01:01:44,870 --> 01:01:46,170
Help me!

986
01:01:47,240 --> 01:01:48,280
What was that?

987
01:01:48,840 --> 01:01:50,580
You heard that, right?

988
01:01:50,850 --> 01:01:53,610
- Yes.
- That was a woman screaming, right?

989
01:01:53,680 --> 01:01:56,720
Yes. Wait. Jin Ah!

990
01:01:57,690 --> 01:01:59,350
Jin Ah! Oh Jin Ah!

991
01:02:02,420 --> 01:02:04,360
- Why, you...
- Come on.

992
01:02:06,130 --> 01:02:08,260
Drop the knife.
Drop it, or I'll shoot.

993
01:02:08,430 --> 01:02:12,070
You take one more step,
and this woman dies. Got it?

994
01:02:13,470 --> 01:02:14,470
Drop your gun.

995
01:02:16,270 --> 01:02:17,640
Drop the gun! Darn it.

996
01:02:18,170 --> 01:02:20,910
Just shoot him.
What are you waiting for? Shoot!

997
01:02:33,890 --> 01:02:36,120
This witch has a death wish.
You punk!

998
01:02:46,370 --> 01:02:47,540
Stay still, you jerk!

999
01:02:56,110 --> 01:02:57,150
Are you okay?

1000
01:02:59,850 --> 01:03:01,980
Are you okay? Are you hurt?
Are you hurt anywhere?

1001
01:03:02,050 --> 01:03:03,520
I'm okay.

1002
01:03:05,020 --> 01:03:06,490
Don't go. It's dangerous.

1003
01:03:08,290 --> 01:03:09,290
Look at me.

1004
01:03:09,920 --> 01:03:11,730
I'm a police officer.

1005
01:03:12,130 --> 01:03:16,660
Jin Ah, go inside, lock the door,
and don't come out. All right?

1006
01:03:18,970 --> 01:03:19,970
Wait! But...

1007
01:03:20,840 --> 01:03:21,940
Don't get hurt.

1008
01:03:22,570 --> 01:03:23,570
Please.

1009
01:03:36,150 --> 01:03:39,050
Who are you? Who the heck are you?

1010
01:03:39,350 --> 01:03:41,960
- Get out of the way!
- Jeong Han, he has a knife!

1011
01:03:42,220 --> 01:03:46,390
What did you do to Jin Ah?
What did you do? You jerk!

1012
01:03:47,130 --> 01:03:51,370
- Out of my way, or I'll stab you!
- Jeong Han, stop it. I'm scared.

1013
01:03:51,430 --> 01:03:55,170
Hey! How dare you wave a knife
around here in Onjeong?

1014
01:03:55,240 --> 01:03:59,440
- You're going down today.
- Hey, Jeong Han!

1015
01:04:01,080 --> 01:04:04,010
Hey! Dong Ik!
Call the cops! Call now!

1016
01:04:05,780 --> 01:04:08,680
Darn it!

1017
01:04:09,650 --> 01:04:12,120
- Over here! Here!
- Hey, Officer, over here!

1018
01:04:12,420 --> 01:04:13,790
- Here!
- Get out of the way! Darn it!

1019
01:04:14,060 --> 01:04:15,720
No!

1020
01:04:26,000 --> 01:04:27,130
Darn it!

1021
01:04:31,740 --> 01:04:35,210
Hey, Dong Ik! Hey!

1022
01:04:35,480 --> 01:04:39,450
Dong Ik! Stay with me! Dong Ik!

1023
01:04:39,780 --> 01:04:43,450
Dong Ik! Stay with me! Dong Ik!

1024
01:05:10,310 --> 01:05:12,910
(Recipe For Love)

1025
01:05:12,980 --> 01:05:17,080
I almost got hit by your mom's car.
But she didn't even apologize.

1026
01:05:17,180 --> 01:05:20,390
- She treated me like a weirdo.
- Oh, really?

1027
01:05:20,450 --> 01:05:23,220
- Dong Ik shielded me from a knife.
- A knife?

1028
01:05:23,290 --> 01:05:25,730
It's a protective instinct.
His body reacted without thinking.

1029
01:05:25,790 --> 01:05:27,700
So, does that mean
he always cared about me that much?

1030
01:05:28,330 --> 01:05:31,570
I love flowers. It's the first time
anyone's ever given me any.

1031
01:05:32,070 --> 01:05:34,670
I worry about you, and I miss you.

1032
01:05:35,270 --> 01:05:36,670
I really like you.

1033
01:05:37,640 --> 01:05:39,710
I couldn't really sleep.
I was too excited.

1034
01:05:40,640 --> 01:05:43,940
- Excuse me?
- Ji Hu's phone's been off.

1035
01:05:44,010 --> 01:05:45,750
Go to the police station right now
and file a report.

1036
01:05:45,750 --> 01:05:46,810
Min Ji Hu!

1037
01:05:47,420 --> 01:05:48,880
Hey, do you happen to know
where Ji Hu is?
